	<string id="escape_trader_repair_0">
		<text>Can you Repair my Equipment?</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_1">
		<text>Ahh! You mean the rifle in the clamp. Yes, I'm fixing it up. So, what do you need repaired? I warn you - it's not cheap. The more damage, the more the repair will cost.\n \nRepair list:</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_3">
		<text>Repair my primary weapon.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_2">
		<text>Repair my secondary weapon.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_4">
		<text>Repair my armor.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_5">
		<text>Damn, I don't have enough money. I'll be back later.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_6">
		<text>Wait, I'll do it in a moment...\n \nReady!!!</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_7">
		<text>Ehh! Marked One, I see you've had some close encounters... Let me fix this up for you...\n \nOk! Here it is, almost like new!</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_8">
		<text>Excellent work. See you later.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_9">
		<text>The work of a master, I have spent my money well. Thanks, bye.</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_10">
		<text>Can you repair something else?</text>
	</string>
	<string id="escape_trader_repair_11">
		<text>Ok, let me see.\n \nRepair list:</text>
	</string>
	
